This directory contains auxiliary files not directly used
by MOLMOL.

    pov*:       Some shell scripts for more conveniently running
                POV-Ray with files produced by MOLMOL. See the
                comments in the files for details.
                povray.ini is a suggested INI file for POV-Ray,
                it is used by the shell scripts.

    arial.ttf:  TrueType font definition, this font is used by
                the POV-Ray files generated with the PlotPov
                command of MOLMOL. It must be in the search path
                of POV-Ray when the file is rendered, you would
                typically copy it into the directory where the
                POV-Ray include files reside (like e. g.
                /usr/local/lib/povray3).

    symbol.ttf: TrueType font definition, this font is used by
                the POV-Ray files generated with the PlotPov
                command of MOLMOL. It must be in the search path
                of POV-Ray when the file is rendered, you would
                typically copy it into the directory where the
                POV-Ray include files reside (like e. g.
                /usr/local/lib/povray3).

    psgamma.c:  C program for doing gamma correction on PostScript
                files. This can be compiled and used as filter
                inside a print alias. A factor between 0.5 and
                1.0 is necessary for most common printers.
    
    stereo:     Shell script to switch the stereo mode of the
                monitor on an SGI system.

    upl2mac:    Shell script to convert an upper limit file to a
                MOLMOL macro.

    ColorList:  Much longer list of colors than the one used
                by default as setup/ColorList.
    
    mol.ico:    A Windows icon that can be used for MOLMOL dump
		files.
